properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A prolonged period of very cold wind chills is expected. A bitterly cold airmass moving southward out of the high arctic will bring temperatures of -35 to -40 to parts of the eastern Arctic. These temperatures will combine with light to moderate winds to produce dangerous wind chills near -55 at times throughout the remainder of the weekend. ### Extreme cold puts everyone at risk. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Weather Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Winter Weather Travel Advisory in effect for tonight. Local lake effect flurries impacting highway 17 from Terrace Bay to Wawa will give additional local amounts of 5 to 10 centimetres through tonight. Visibility will be reduced at times in heavy flurries. Cold temperatures combined with rapidly accumulating snow on roads may produce hazardous conditions at times. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A prolonged period of very cold wind chills is expected. The coldest wind chill values will be near minus 55. Wind chill values near minus 55 are expected throughout the weekend. ### Extreme cold puts everyone at risk. Risks are greater for young children, older adults, people with chronic illnesses, people working or exercising outdoors, and those without proper shelter. Watch for cold related symptoms: shortness of breath, chest pain, muscle pain and weakness, numbness and colour change in fingers and toes. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Summary:
Description: A prolonged period of very cold wind chills is expected. A bitterly cold airmass covering the high arctic will bring temperatures of -35 to -40 to northern Baffin Island. These temperatures will combine with winds up to 10 km/h to produce wind chills at times colder than the -50 warning threshold throughout the remainder of the weekend. ### Extreme cold puts everyone at risk. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.
